A link like this:

{code}
[`example`](http://www.example.com)
{code}

Should render as a link with {{monspaced}} text.  Instead it renders as the following broken HTML:

{code}
<a href="<a href="http://www.example.com" rel="nofollow"  >http://www.example.com</a>"><code>example</code></a>
{code}

Live example:

[{{example}}|http://www.example.com]

[{{like this}}|http://example.com] which renders as of this writing as

{code}
http://example.com">like this
{code}

Found on https://bitbucket.org/S11001001/record-map

Today, when I started work again after the weekend, I discovered that links in descriptions of my issues are no longer being rendered correctly. Example of rendering:\\
!1245696402-incorrect-link-rendering.PNG|thumbnail!

Source markdown:

{code}
#!text

The most likely cause of this is the fact that [`mysqli::__construct()`](http://php.net/manual/en/mysqli.construct.php) does not accept the host name together with port number as in `meta2535376233.db.2535376.hostedresource.com:3306`, as opposed to [`mysql_connect()`](http://php.net/manual/en/function.mysql-connect.php), but accepts the port as a separate parameter.
{code}

Adding a {{callback}} parameter to the URL should change the Content-Type *from* {{application/json; charset=utf-8}} *to* {{application/javascript; charset=utf-8}}

You can test this using:

{code}
curl -s -I https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/snippets/dvdsmpsn/y6Eeg/?callback=xxx | grep "^Content-Type:"
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
{code}

This is wrong and should instead be {{Content-Type: application/javascript; charset=utf-8}} like in most of your other REST APIs.

Compare this to another (correctly working) REST API:

Standard JSON call:

{code}
curl -s -I &#x27;https://api.bitbucket.org/1.0/repositories/dvdsmpsn/pii-viewer-for-google-analytics/issues?status=open&status=new&#x27;| grep "^Content-Type:"
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
{code}

JSONP call with callback parameter

{code}
curl -s -I &#x27;https://api.bitbucket.org/1.0/repositories/dvdsmpsn/pii-viewer-for-google-analytics/issues?callback=xxx&status=open&status=new&#x27;| grep "^Content-Type:"
Content-Type: application/javascript; charset=utf-8
{code}

